    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - OVERHAUL PROCEDURES - CLEANING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLEANING</title>
        <para>After disassembly and before attempting inspection, clean parts as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Steel parts with ground or polished surface:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Wash in suitable cleaning solvent.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Rinse thoroughly to remove cleaning solution.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Dry parts with clean rag.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean castings, forgings and other rough-surface parts: Wire brush or steam-clean areas that
                are susceptible to accumulation of mud, road dirt, salt, etc.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Do not use gasoline to clean parts. Gasoline can explode, causing serious physical injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
